The film condition is not perfect in many places, but never was.
In various scenes/cuts there is obvious deterioration or 'dirt' on the cell.
This is true of every print I have seen so it's no surprise here.
Overall the video quality is clean with some noise (it was 1985).
The audio is exceptional and particularly enjoyable is the commentary from
Terry Gilliam, a must listen.

